# UI / Templates Rules

## Jinja organisation

```
app/templates/
  layouts/     # base.html (app shell), auth_base.html
  partials/    # sidebar, topnav, flash_messages
  <feature>/   # auth, dashboard, mission, study_plan, analytics, settings, errors
```

- Authenticated pages extend `layouts/base.html`.
- Auth pages extend `layouts/auth_base.html`.
- Keep feature templates in the matching folder; wizard steps stay under `study_plan/`.
- Pass `title` for the document title block when practical.
- Reuse partials instead of duplicating chrome.

## CSS

- Global styles: `app/static/css/app.css`.
- Wizard-specific: `app/static/css/wizard.css` (include via `extra_head` when needed).
- Prefer extending existing tokens/classes over introducing a parallel design system.
- Bootstrap 5.3 is provided via CDN in the layout — do not vendor a second framework without a milestone decision.

## JavaScript

- Shared: `app/static/js/app.js`.
- Feature-specific files (e.g. `mission.js`) for isolated behaviour.
- Progressive enhancement: critical flows should not depend on fragile client-only state.
- Read CSRF from `<meta name="csrf-token">` when posting via JS.

## Do not

- Embed large inline scripts in templates when a static file is clearer.
- Bypass CSP assumptions casually (see security headers in `app/__init__.py`).
- Put business rules (ordering, mastery math) in templates — compute in services/routes.
